eriments ‣ Cover First, Disagree Softly: Rethinking Mismatch-First Active Learning for Frame-Level Audio Classification\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">§4.1</span></a>.\n514\t</span>\n515\t</li>\n516\t<li id=\"bib.bib11\" class=\"ltx_bibitem ltx_bib_inproceedings\">\n517\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_bib_key ltx_role_refnum ltx_tag_bibitem\">[6]</span>\n518\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_author\">Y. Gal, R. Islam, and Z. Ghahramani</span><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_year\"> (2017)</span>\n519\t</span>\n520\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_title\">Deep Bayesian active learning with image data</span>.\n521\t</span>\n522\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\">In <span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_inbook\">Proc. ICML</span>,\n523\t</span>\n524\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_pages\"> pp. 1183–1192</span>.\n525\t</span>\n526\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock ltx_bib_cited\">Cited by: <a href=\"#S1.p2.1\" title=\"1 Introduction ‣ Cover First, Disagree Softly: Rethinking Mismatch-First Active Learning for Frame-Level Audio Classification\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">§1</span></a>.\n527\t</span>\n528\t</li>\n529\t<li id=\"bib.bib25\" class=\"ltx_bibitem ltx_bib_article\">\n530\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_bib_key ltx_role_refnum ltx_tag_bibitem\">[7]</span>\n531\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_author\">D. Garreau, W. Jitkrittum, and M. Kanagawa</span><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_year\"> (2017)</span>\n532\t</span>\n533\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_title\">Large sample analysis of the median heuristic</span>.\n534\t</span>\n535\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_bib_journal\">arXiv preprint arXiv:1707.07269</span>.\n536\t</span>\n537\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock ltx_bib_cited\">Cited by: <a href=\"#S3.SS1.p1.8\" title=\"3.1 Mismatch-weighted facility location ‣ 3 Cover first, 